title: Trump Vows to Boost Reciprocal Tariffs on Imports If Reelected
description: Donald Trump said he will impose tit-for-tat tariffs if he is reelected president, reiterating one of his isolationist policy goals that has already raised concern at home and overseas.

title: Trudeau, Meloni to Establish Roadmap for Enhanced Cooperation
description: The prime ministers of Canada and Italy announced a roadmap to deepen the relationship between the two nations.

title: Yellen Praises Ties With Chile, a Vital Part of EV Supply Chain
description: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen championed robust US relations with Chile on Saturday, saying that the two nations could help one another achieve goals involving climate and energy.

title: Trump Wins Missouri Caucus in March to Republican Nomination
description: Former President Donald Trump swept the latest Republican presidential nominating contest on Saturday, beating rival Nikki Haley in Missouri.

title: Chile Pledges to Investigate Death of Kidnapped Venezuelan
description: Chile’s government vowed an investigation into the death of a kidnapped Venezuelan refugee Ronald Ojeda in Santiago until the crime is “fully clarified and punished with the utmost severity,” Interior Minister Carolina Toha said Saturday.

title: US, Jordan Make First Joint Airdrop of 38,000 Meals Into Gaza
description: The US and Jordan worked together to deliver supplies to Gaza on Saturday using military cargo planes, making good on President Joe Biden’s promise of emergency humanitarian aid.

title: In California’s Heated Senate Race, a Trump Voter Has a Chance at Snagging a Spot
description: Adam Schiff is in the lead, and a Donald Trump-voting former baseball star may also prevail, thanks to some unusual gambits.

title: Latest International Effort to Help Haiti Greeted by Doubts
description: A new international effort is under way to reverse Haiti’s rapid descent into lawlessness, but disagreements, tepid contributions, and delays in deploying police forces have raised concerns that yet another mission to rescue the Caribbean nation is doomed to fail.

title: Pro-Palestine Protesters Deny Extremism as They Target Barclays Branches
description: Pro-Palestine protests continued across England and Wales on Saturday following Rishi Sunak's warning that demonstrations and democracy itself were being targeted by extremists.

title: Iran’s Parliamentary Election Turnout Slumps to Historic Low
description: Iran’s parliamentary elections saw a decline in voter participation to historic lows, according to estimates published by state-run media, in a vote hailed by authorities as a triumph for the ruling establishment regardless of its outcome.

title: Modi to Contest From Varanasi as BJP Kickstarts Vote Campaign
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will again contest from the holy Hindu city of Varanasi, topping the first list of candidates which gives his Bharatiya Janata Party a headstart over the opposition alliance that’s still negotiating seat shares.

title: Germany Probes Military Security Leak After Russian Wiretapping
description: Germany’s defense ministry is probing a suspected intelligence leak after Russian media published a conversation between high-ranking air force officials about the possible deployment of Taurus long-range missiles in Ukraine.

title: Fertilizer Ship Attacked by Houthis Last Month Sinks in Red Sea
description: A commercial ship attacked by Houthi militants in February has sunk in the Red Sea, Yemen’s internationally recognized government said, risking an environmental disaster in the area.

title: Gaza Cease-fire Talks to Resume in Egypt on Sunday, Reuters Says
description: Negotiations between Israel and Hamas on a ceasefire in Gaza are due to resume in Cairo on Sunday, Reuters reported, citing two Egyptian security sources.

title: South Korean Doctors Continue Walkout as Global Body Weighs In
description: South Korean trainee doctors continued their walkout Saturday with little sign of them returning to work as a global body of physicians supported their protest of a government plan to increase medical school intakes.

title: Ukraine Hit by Drones as Possible UAV Strikes St. Petersburg
description: At least three deaths were reported from Russian drone attacks in southern and eastern Ukraine early Saturday, while a UAV was suspected of hitting a residential building in Russia’s St. Petersburg, hundreds of miles from the border.

title: Iran’s Switch to Highly Sought Civil Nuclear Fuel Seen as a Ploy
description: Iran’s decision to reduce its stockpile of near bomb-grade uranium in favor of producing a specialized fuel for advanced civil nuclear reactors may be a negotiating tactic, according to western officials.

title: Jeremy Hunt Is Trapped Between Voters and Markets in Crunch UK Budget
description: Jeremy Hunt faces a difficult balancing act in his annual budget next week, under pressure to deliver eye-catching tax cuts to give a pre-election boost to his ailing Conservative Party, yet also hamstrung by the fragility of the UK public finances.

title: Sunak Struggles to Halt UK Tories Drifting Toward Rival Badenoch
description: Rishi Sunak’s chances of winning the next UK election have already been written off by most in Westminster. Yet close allies worry the challenge is becoming even harder than it should be because one of own his Cabinet ministers is positioning to succeed him as Conservative Party leader.

title: China Vice President Urges US Firms to Find New Areas to Team Up
description: China’s vice president urged businesses from the world’s two largest economies to boost cooperation and safeguard global supply chains, as Beijing and Washington try to work through their differences.

title: Milei Seeks Pact With Political Leaders in Bid to Save Reforms
description: President Javier Milei proposed a pact with Argentina’s powerful province governors and other top political leaders as he seeks to protect his austerity measures and liberalizing reforms from an increasingly hostile congress.

title: Australia to Consult on Meta’s Move to End Facebook News
description: Australia will consult with media organizations after Meta Platforms Inc. said it would wind down the Facebook News tab from April.

title: In Sync With AMLO, Mexico Frontrunner Proposes Boosting Welfare
description: Mexico’s presidential candidate for the ruling Morena party Claudia Sheinbaum launched her campaign with a series of proposals to build out the welfare programs that underpin the popularity of the current president, pitching herself as someone who would build on his legacy.

title: Man Charged With Attacking Police in Times Square Was Misidentified, DA Says
description: NEW YORK (AP) — A Venezuelan man who became the subject of national attention for allegedly kicking a police officer in Times Square, then flipping off news cameras on his way out of court, was cleared of wrongdoing on Friday after prosecutors concluded he played no role in the attack.

title: Hunt to Require Pension Funds to Disclose Level of UK Investment
description: The Treasury will require pensions funds to publicly disclose how much they invest in UK businesses, part of government efforts to spur them to boost investments in UK assets.
